<br /><br />Ultimately, the biggest adjustment for teachers will not be in understanding the functions of tablet devices but in incorporating them into their teaching styles, Backon notes.
<br /><br />&quot;Most teachers are accustomed to a teacher-centric classroom where the teacher is the center of the classroom and the giver of knowledge,&quot; he says. &quot;Now, the iPad allows us to put the responsibility of learning into the hands of the students.&quot;
